Jocelyn,

I&#39;ve used one step reactions with the C++ code and it works fine.  I  
haven&#39;t used it with the Matlab code.

The line in the cti file should look something like this:

reaction( &quot; 2 JP8 + 33 O2 =&gt; 22 CO2 + 22 H2O &quot; ,  [1.45e10, 0.0,   
124.7e6],  order = &quot;JP8:0.75 O2:1.0 &quot;)

The  xml file should contain the reaction step like this.

   &lt;reactionData id=&quot;reaction_data&quot;&gt;

     &lt;!-- reaction 0001    --&gt;
     &lt;reaction reversible=&quot;no&quot; id=&quot;0001&quot;&gt;
       &lt;equation&gt;2 JP8 + 33 O2 =] 22 CO2 + 22 H2O &lt;/equation&gt;
       &lt;order species=&quot;JP8&quot;&gt;0.75&lt;/order&gt;
       &lt;order species=&quot;O2&quot;&gt;1.0&lt;/order&gt;
       &lt;rateCoeff&gt;
         &lt;Arrhenius&gt;
            &lt;A&gt;1.450000E+010&lt;/A&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;0.0&lt;/b&gt;
            &lt;E units=&quot;J/kmol&quot;&gt;124700000.000000&lt;/E&gt;
         &lt;/Arrhenius&gt;
       &lt;/rateCoeff&gt;
       &lt;reactants&gt;JP8:2 O2:33&lt;/reactants&gt;
       &lt;products&gt;H2O:22 CO2:22&lt;/products&gt;
     &lt;/reaction&gt;
   &lt;/reactionData&gt;


Good luck.

Karl

